<subSubSection pageId="15" pageNumber="16" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1437,474,2011]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,266,474,499]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. Males are easily distinguished from other species in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="O. Pickard-Cambridge" authorityYear="1869" box="[889,1007,474,499]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Pholcus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ceylonicus">
<emphasis box="[889,1007,474,499]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">ceylonicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group by shape of genital bulb (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 73–78" captionStartId="20.[151,264,1878,1901]" captionTargetBox="[161,1424,412,1846]" captionTargetId="figure@20.[151,1436,409,1858]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="FIGURES 73–78. Left genital bulbs in prolateral, dorsal, and retrolateral views. 73–75. Pholcus ceylonicus O. Pickard- Cambridge, 1869 (from Kandy, ZFMK Ar 20039); asterisks mark small sclerotized process close to proximal bulbal sclerite (Fig. 73) and distinctive conical projection (Fig. 74); arrow points at distinctive retrolateral membrane. 76–78. P. metta sp. n. (from Dimbulagala, ZFMK Ar 20049). Abbreviations: a, ‘appendix’ (main bulbal process); b, genital bulb; e, embolus; pbs, proximal bulbal sclerite. Scales lines: 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2625054/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Figs 76–78</figureCitation>
): distinctive main bulbal process (‘appendix’), i.e. large sclerotized process without retrolateral membrane and retrolateral conical projection (in contrast to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="O. Pickard-Cambridge" authorityYear="1869" box="[718,866,546,571]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Pholcus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ceylonicus">
<emphasis box="[718,866,546,571]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">P. ceylonicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), narrower in dorsal view than in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Huber" authorityYear="2019" box="[1267,1428,548,571]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Pholcus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="puranappui">
<emphasis box="[1267,1428,548,571]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">P. puranappui</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; without prolateral process (in contrast to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Huber" authorityYear="2019" box="[609,673,583,606]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Pholcus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="uva">
<emphasis box="[609,673,583,606]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">P. uva</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); distinguished from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Huber" authorityYear="2019" box="[917,982,583,606]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Pholcus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="uva">
<emphasis box="[917,982,583,606]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">P. uva</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
also by shape of procursus (
<figureCitation box="[1302,1432,582,607]" captionStart="FIGURES 65–72" captionStartId="19.[151,264,1640,1663]" captionTargetBox="[154,1435,194,1607]" captionTargetId="figure@19.[151,1436,193,1619]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURES 65–72. Left procursi in retrolateral (upper row) and dorsal views. 65–66. Pholcus ceylonicus O. Pickard- Cambridge, 1869 (from Kandy, ZFMK Ar 20039). 67–68. P. metta sp. n. (from Dimbulagala, ZFMK Ar 20049); arrows point at subdistal dorsal process, asterisks mark prolateral processes. 69–70. Pholcus puranappui sp. n. (from Dematagala, ZFMK Ar 20051). 71–72. P. uva sp. n. (from Inginiyagala, ZFMK Ar 20055). At different scales." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2625052/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Figs 67–68</figureCitation>
; narrower and with subdistal dorsal process). Females are distinguished from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="O. Pickard-Cambridge" authorityYear="1869" box="[1043,1191,618,643]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Pholcus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ceylonicus">
<emphasis box="[1043,1191,618,643]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">P. ceylonicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Huber" authorityYear="2019" box="[1252,1320,620,643]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Pholcus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="uva">
<emphasis box="[1252,1320,620,643]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">P. uva</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by larger posterior excavation of pre-epigynal plate (
<figureCitation box="[639,723,654,679]" captionStart="FIGURES 85–88" captionStartId="22.[151,264,1360,1383]" captionTargetBox="[157,1430,193,1339]" captionTargetId="figure@22.[151,1436,193,1339]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="FIGURES 85–88. Epigyna in ventral views, all at same scale. 85. Pholcus ceylonicus O. Pickard-Cambridge, 1869 (from Kandy, ZFMK Ar 20039). 86. P. metta sp. n. (from Dimbulagala, ZFMK Ar 20049). 87. Pholcus puranappui sp. n. (from Dematagala, ZFMK Ar 20051). 88. P. uva sp. n. (from Inginiyagala, ZFMK Ar 20055). Abbreviations: ep, epigynal plate; k, ‘knob’ (median epigynal process); pep, pre-epigynal plate. Scale line: 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2625058/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Fig. 86</figureCitation>
); from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Huber" authorityYear="2019" box="[807,966,655,678]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Pholcus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="puranappui">
<emphasis box="[807,966,655,678]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">P. puranappui</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by narrower pre-epigynal plate (compare 
<figureCitation box="[151,281,690,715]" captionStart="FIGURES 85–88" captionStartId="22.[151,264,1360,1383]" captionTargetBox="[157,1430,193,1339]" captionTargetId="figure@22.[151,1436,193,1339]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="FIGURES 85–88. Epigyna in ventral views, all at same scale. 85. Pholcus ceylonicus O. Pickard-Cambridge, 1869 (from Kandy, ZFMK Ar 20039). 86. P. metta sp. n. (from Dimbulagala, ZFMK Ar 20049). 87. Pholcus puranappui sp. n. (from Dematagala, ZFMK Ar 20051). 88. P. uva sp. n. (from Inginiyagala, ZFMK Ar 20055). Abbreviations: ep, epigynal plate; k, ‘knob’ (median epigynal process); pep, pre-epigynal plate. Scale line: 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2625058/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Figs 86–87</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="15" pageNumber="16" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1437,474,2011]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,326,726,751]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Etymology</emphasis>
. The species name is derived from the Pāli word 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Huber" authorityYear="2019" box="[934,996,727,750]" class="Arachnida" family="Pholcidae" genus="Pholcus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="metta">
<emphasis box="[934,996,727,750]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">mettā</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, one of the four Buddhist virtues or brahmavihāras (active good will towards all); noun in apposition.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
